e also know that Sun, Moon, Mars, Mercury, Jupiter, Venus, Saturn, Rahu and=
 Ketu are personifications of soul, mind, energy/initiative/drive, learning=
 spirit, wisdom/discrimination, spirit of enjoyment/being happy, patience/d=
iscipline, spirit of
 innovation/breaking barriers and detachment (respecti=
vely).=C2=A0Correspondingly, each avatara is an expression of that aspect o=
f Supreme in a perfected form. Each story is an example of how that aspect =
operates.=C2=A0Lord Rama's story is a perfected example of how soul operate=
s. Lord Krishna's story is a perfected example of how mind operates. Lord V=
amana's story is a perfected example of how wisdom/discrimination operates.=
 Lord Narasimha's story is a perfected example of how energy/drive/initiati=
ve operates.=C2=A0*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=
=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0Now, let us remember one basic thing.=
 Soul in us, mind in us, energy in us, learning spirit in us, wisdom in us,=
 happiness in us, discipline/patience in us - all these are different manif=
estations of the same Self. However, when Self manifests as these different=
 aspects, it has different qualities and plays different roles. There is no=
 comparison between them.=C2=A0We MAY focus on one aspect of us first, perf=
ect it and then
 perfect other aspects through it. But, we need balance bet=
ween all aspects in the end. Similarly, these different aspects of Supreme =
Being are incomparable and are in a balance working together in the Cosmos.=
