on king with many great qualities.=C2=A0Wisdom/discrimination makes one hum=
ble and unassuming. When one is doing good work but tainted with demonic qu=
alities (e.g. pride or attachment), one's discrimination is not pleased unt=
il that pride is suppressed. When wisdom fills one's entire consciousness, =
